@node 08248.003
Subject: Re: my Heretic2 qwestionz....
From: Hans-Joerg Frieden <hfrieden@uni-trier.de>
Date: Tue, 1 Aug 2000 00:10:01 +0200 (CEST)

On Mon, 31 Jul 2000, DJNick wrote:

> I was very very happy :)) to have latest original game :)))) and I supported
> you, the programmers :)))

Thanks :) Glad you like it...
 
> Why GL_texturemode is not set  to 'linear' by default? Is it slowing
> down a game? 
 
No, it doesn't  really slow down. Actually, the  gl_texturemode is set
to gl_linear_mip_linear  by default, meaning  trilinear filtering, but
although the ViRGE does support this, the Permedia2 doesn't, so that's
why it turns out unfiltered...

> - Also: why this GL_command isn't documented in H2 little book? I accidently
> remembered it from GLQuake :) After that, ingame graphics started to look
> stunning.

The booklet  is almost  the same  as the PC  version, and  this didn't
include those variables either... I know, weak excuse :)

> - Game is incredible! Pity Permedia2 is slow :( And 166mhz isn't the fastest 060
> I could buy. But it is playable...

166MHz? 060? Typo I guess ;-)
Yes, I hope that upcoming PCI solutions will clear up the situation a bit. 

> - Music is FANTASTIC! :))))

Yes, very atmospheric isn't it...

> - Ok, next thing is slow playing intro animation[s]:

I'm afraid the video use AHI  for sound playback, and this can be slow
especially on 040. To speed things up, go to the AHI prefs and set the
# of channels  to 1 or 2,  Mix freq. to  22050 or lower, and  select a
FAST 8 Bit mode with no "++"  in the name. Also, make sure to give the
CDRom  a bit  of additional  buffers. I'm  afraid, though,  that ATAPI
devices use  CPU time for  reading, this gives  them a hard  time. You
might copy  the movies (space permitting)  to the disk  by copying the
contents     of     Heretic_IIB:base/video     to    the     directory
HereticII/Base/Video  on   your  hard  disk,  and  set   the  CD  Path
accrodingly (i.e. point it  to XXX:HereticII or wherever you installed
the game).

> - Music [atapi.device unit1 here] starts playing 1-2 minutes later after the
> game is started [level1]. Is it supposed to work this way?

No, it  should start right away.  Did you install the  update from the
web page?

> - Any 'tip' for speedUP ingame framerate? What is 'paletted textures' option
> for?

If  you  have   enough  memory,  raise  the  caches.   Check  out  our
troubleshooting guide on the web page, it has a few hints.

> - I was reading after H2 is released that some people had problems with the
> game: they couldn't start the game more times than once after it is installed.
> Strange :) but here I can start the game anytime and without any problem. [is
> something wrong with my Amiga configuration?] ;))

These issues should have been fixed with the update...

> (I have CGX4.1 and 64MB ram [before starting H2, I have ~57MB free memory].
> Tomorrow morning I'll install 128 MB [yep, I upgraded to 128MB for just 150DM] :)) I
> hope it will solve some problems :)

Additional memory will help a lot...

> Any ideas?

The issues with  video are caused by the  context switches and general
CPU load  of the system, especially  obvious on IDE...  Try the above,
this *should* help...
 
