On 1 Jul 2000, Rolf Max Rotvel wrote:
> My point is: You're not offering CDDA support at all at the moment as
> far as I can tell. cdplay.library support will be an added bonus
> for those with a CDROM drive that supports CDDA. 

CDDA means Compact Disk Digital Audio. That's what we support. It's replay
of audio CDs. It's done by just issuing a "play" command to the CD-ROM.
That's exactly the same what cdplay.library offers, nothing else, so I
don't see a point in using cdplay.library. 

If you refer to CDDA as reading audio data over the scsi bus, and playing
them over the Amigas audio, this won't happen. There are just a handful of
configurations out there that could handle that, and it would lead to a
lot more overhead due to context switches. Another thing is that the
time spent in a Warp3D lock will also prevent a steady stream of data from
the CD-ROM, which will make it impossible to play back without jumps.

Regards,
