On Sat, 1 Jul 2000, Stefano Marturano wrote:

> Is 320x240 such an effort for the Permedia2 ?

It is.  I have  written a  small test program  that verifies  the fill
rate. The  problem is that Heretic  II uses at least  two passes (some
effects like the  Ring of Repulsion spell use up to  10), and only the
first pass is done *without*  alpha blending. Only that enabling alpha
blending reduces  the fill rate by  approx. 60%. So  you are basically
not dealing with  a 320x240 screen alone, you  have two times overdraw
of  the full  frame  (plus  what is  discarded  by ZBuffering),  where
everything  after the first  draw is  done at  a greatly  reduced fill
rate... 

