On Tue, 18 Jul 2000, Steven Dobbs wrote:
> I was wondering if it was possible to render an RGB texture onto a coloured
> surface as in a blend without using an RGBA texture map. is this possible.
> I need this effect for shield effects.

This is possible, just by setting the appropriate alpha value as the alpha
component of the vertices. Alpha blending must be enabled, of course.

Remeber, though, that the Permedia 2 is not able to interpolate the Alpha
value over the polygon. It uses the alpha of the first vertex it
encouters, which is normally the one which is at the lower end of the
triangle...

